<AbstractNarration>0081808  Linden/UCSD&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;A study will be made of the interaction of vortices in stratified &lt;br/&gt;rotating flows.  The study will consist of laboratory experiments &lt;br/&gt;conducted on a rotating table.  Vortices will be generated by pumping &lt;br/&gt;flow in and out through the sides of the experimental tank in a number &lt;br/&gt;of different source/sink configurations.  Experiments will be made in &lt;br/&gt;tanks with cylindrical and annular geometries.  Sophisticated optical &lt;br/&gt;flow measurement techniques will be used to obtain flow velocities at &lt;br/&gt;a variety of depths.  The aim of the study is to build up an &lt;br/&gt;understanding of the rotationally dominated, large-scale turbulence &lt;br/&gt;prevalent in the ocean.  Interactions between individual vortices will &lt;br/&gt;be studied, together with the way in which multiple interactions &lt;br/&gt;between continuously forced vortices give rise to mean circulations.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
